article.description: — Dionte Bostick scored 20 points as CSU Northridge beat Chicago State 74-64 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Bostick scores 20, helps Cal State Northridge top Chicago State 74-64
article.linkText: Bostick scores 20, helps Cal State Northridge top Chicago State 74-64
article.story: CHICAGO -- — Dionte Bostick scored 20 points as CSU Northridge beat Chicago State 74-64 on Tuesday night. Bostick added five rebounds for the Matadors (2-1). De'Sean Allen-Eikens scored 18 points while shooting 5 for 9 (1 for 3 from 3-point range) and 7 of 10 from the free throw line, and added five rebounds. Keonte Jones had 13 points and shot 6 of 10 from the field and 1 for 3 from the line. Wesley Cardet Jr. led the way for the Cougars (1-3) with 21 points. Jahsean Corbett added 11 points and eight rebounds for Chicago State. In addition, Brent Davis finished with nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
